* Avondale Mills Inc., Sylacauga, Ala., a fabrics and yarns company, said John G. Hudson, its president and chief operating officer, will retire on Aug. 31. The company promoted Richard H. Monk Jr. to executive vice president and said he was expected to succeed Mr. Hudson. The company also announced the resignation of George B. Smith, corporate vice president and president of Avondale Yarns, and said C. Michael Billingsley would replace him.

* Cleveland-Cliffs Inc., Cleveland, a mining company, appointed Gordon N. Carlson senior vice president for operations.

* Cycle Industries, Anaheim, Calif., an apparel manufacturer, named its chief executive, Jonathan Edelstein, as chairman.

* El Paso Electric Co., a utility, named Curtis L. Hoskins executive vice president and chief operating officer.